# Always push after commit

In this project (MRA Map Revival / ogn), after any `git commit`, immediately `git push` to the tracked remote branch.

- Do this by default without waiting to be asked.
- Use a normal `git push` (or `git push -u origin HEAD` when the branch has no upstream yet).
- Do not force-push unless the user explicitly asks.
- Commit and push remain separate commands (PowerShell: no `&&`, no heredoc).
